	 <div id="droite2">
	 
             <h2 id="centretitremaj">Library</h2>
         

	 <div id="block">

<!------------------------>
	
<!------------------------>

	  	  <h3 class="titre3">Description</h3>
<p>Formed in 1990, the <span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr">Minist&egrave;re des Finances</span> library provides employees of the MFQ with a full range of documentary services and responds to requests from outside the Department. It is part of the <span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr">Direction des communications</span> and is a member of the <span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr">R&eacute;seau informatis&eacute; des biblioth&egrave;ques gouvernementales du Qu&eacute;bec</span>
 (computerized network of Qu&eacute;bec government libraries).</p>
<h4 class="titre4">Collection</h4>
<p>The library&rsquo;s collection consists of 41,500&nbsp;monographs and 350&nbsp;periodical titles dealing mainly with finance, public finances, economics and law. It can be consulted using the unified catalogue of Qu&eacute;bec government libraries&nbsp;(CUBIQ).</p>
<h4 class="titre4">CUBIQ</h4>

<p>The library&rsquo;s catalogue is part of the unified catalogue of Qu&eacute;bec government libraries&nbsp;(CUBIQ). CUBIQ searches cover all the collections of the 32 member libraries of the <span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr">R&eacute;seau informatis&eacute; des biblioth&egrave;ques gouvernementales</span> (more than 1,000,000&nbsp;entries).</p>
<p>To restrict the search to the <span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr">
Finances</span> collection, check the &ldquo;Catalogs&rdquo; box and select &ldquo;<span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr">Finances</span>&rdquo;</p>
<p class="decal3"><a title="link to CUBIQ catalogue" href="javascript:LienAccEnExt('http://www.cubiq.ribg.gouv.qc.ca')">CUBIQ</a> <img alt="This link will open in a another window." src="/images/icone_lien-externe.gif" /></p>
<h4 class="titre4">Services available to external clients</h4>

<p>The general public can consult the documents on site. It is a good idea to make an appointment in advance with library personnel.</p>
<p>Documents can be borrowed only through the inter-library loan service of your municipal, college, university or other library.</p>
<h4 class="titre4">Contact information</h4>
<p><span lang="fr" class="strong" xml:lang="fr">Minist&egrave;re des Finances</span>
